<h3>NE Fetch Model</h3>
<p>When wind direction is NE, the fetch along Maui's north shore is maximized, producing well-organized windswell bumps ideal for downwind foiling. The analysis considers:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Period</strong> — longer period windswell (6-8s) = more organized bumps</li>
  <li><strong>Height</strong> — 0.5-1.5m windswell = optimal bump size</li>
  <li><strong>Direction</strong> — NE direction = long fetch = best bump organization</li>
</ul>
<p>All three factors combine into a downwind foiling rating.</p>

