<h2>5. Rain & Precipitation</h2>
<p><code>forecast-nws.mjs</code> + <code>pressure-meteo.mjs</code> + <code>buildPrecipSummary</code></p>

<p>Dual-source precipitation analysis combining NWS and Open-Meteo, with WMO weathercode shower detection and radar confirmation.</p>

<h3>Dual-Source PoP</h3>
<p>Probability of precipitation is averaged from both NWS gridpoint data and Open-Meteo forecasts. Neither source alone is reliable enough for Maui's microclimate.</p>

<h3>Shower Detection</h3>
<p>WMO weathercodes identify shower activity:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Codes <strong>80–82</strong>: Rain showers (slight/moderate/violent)</li>
  <li>Codes <strong>85–86</strong>: Snow showers (rare at sea level)</li>
  <li>Codes <strong>95–99</strong>: Thunderstorms</li>
</ul>

